# Historical PASS entries that no longer form a reproducible regression gate
# because the upstream input is currently non-hermetic, release-shaped, or drift-prone.
#
# Categories of breakage (last verified 2026-04-07 against 17 sampled cases):
#   - Dockerfile expects a pre-built binary in the build context (release tarball
#     workflow): minio, prometheus-node-exporter, prom-prometheus, hashicorp-http-echo,
#     chartmuseum
#   - No Dockerfile in repo at the manifest path: caddy
#   - Upstream Makefile/build broken with current toolchain or missing scripts:
#     mailhog (Go too old for `cmp` package), grafana-loki (`make: no rule for loki`),
#     influxdata-telegraf (postgres C build), influxdata-influxdb (network fetch in step 17),
#     ollama (OCI layer apply network error)
#   - Dockerfile uses `ARG BASE` with no default, requires --build-arg: opa
#   - Build is too heavy to gate on (>10 min, mostly bind-pulls): grafana-grafana
minio-minio
caddyserver-caddy
mailhog-mailhog
prometheus-node-exporter
prom-prometheus
grafana-grafana
grafana-loki
hashicorp-http-echo
chartmuseum-chartmuseum
influxdata-telegraf
influxdata-influxdb
open-policy-agent-opa
ollama-ollama
