# Verified 2026-04-15 re-audit (Agent E): curated FAILs re-classified as genuinely unrescuable.
# - No Dockerfile upstream at pinned SHA: mongoose (source mirror), denoland-deno (devcontainer >4G disk),
#   oakserver-oak (devcontainer), plausible-analytics (compose-only).
# - Upstream rot: racket-lang/koka-lang/vlang (Debian buster EOL, deb.debian.org 404), derailed-k9s
#   (Dockerfile Go 1.25.5 but go.mod 1.25.8 + GOTOOLCHAIN=local).
# - Release-tarball pattern (COPY pre-built binary): hugo, zola.
denoland-deno
derailed-k9s
hugo
koka-lang
mongoose
oakserver-oak
plausible-analytics
racket-lang
vlang
zola
# 2026-04-15 final sweep: failed at build time despite earlier categorization.
# - dive: multi-stage RUN step 3 fails with buildkit-style cache mount not emulated.
# - h2o: CMake mbedcrypto compile exceeds the 900s boot timeout (C++ heavy).
# - huginn: RUN step 14 fails; ruby bundler toolchain fetch flaky.
dive
h2o
huginn  # gocracker Dockerfile parser doesn't expand build-args inside USER directive: huginn does `USER $UID` and step 14's `useradd $UID` parses it as literal "$UID" -> "unknown user". Real upstream-compat bug to fix later.
